author: Tartuffe the Spry Wonder Dog

text: Tartuffe the Spry Wonder Dog Did you actually buy games back then?

@607 Yes. Now that I think about it, NES games were pretty cheap in the mid to late 90's, well after the 4th and even 5th gen were taking over. I remember getting Punch Out and Metroid brand new for like less than 10 bucks. This was like 1995-ish, I think.
author: Tartuffe the Spry Wonder Dog

text:
Tartuffe the Spry Wonder Dog They could've got discounted then, though. ;)
It is possible that Nintendo (and Sega) games were more expensive than other games, of course. Because they were on cartridges and because they were generally higher quality.
@607 I think that was because a lot of people had moved on to the new consoles, and stores were trying to get rid of the old stuff. But yeah, in the 80's NES games were like 50 bucks, iirc.
